                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Would you like to see an authorised system set up for eq players to trade in game items for real cash?
<br />
Yes
<br />
No
<br />
Don't care.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I said no because:
<br />
a) it unfairly benefits those with a large disposable income. 
<br />
b) it will legitimise the organised harvesting and griefing in places like tactics. 
<br />
c) it's not in the spirit of the game.
<br />
d) I think it will affect the in game economy, the preference would be to flog it for real cash over virtual cash. Bazaar prices would then shoot up meaning you get less for higher prices, potentially encouraging more use of Kit for Cash in a self fueling loop.
<br />

<br />
I considered yes because:
<br />
a) It would provide protection against fraudsters.
<br />
b) do I really care if someone spends  their cash on some equipment that makes them happy. 
<br />

<br />
Right going to check this autoduck thing</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
