                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I kinda see this as SOE acknowledging finally that this is something that is going to happen regardless of what they do.  The gaming companies have lost lawsuit after lawsuit over selling of in game items.  They can't win under US law.  But SOE does spend time handling clean up when these tranfers go wrong.  Legitimizing it will allow them to put things in place to make this clean up easier.  Also, my guess is they will take a bit off the top 5-10% like Player Auctions and "get a piece of the action".
<br />

<br />
Sounds like sound financial logic to me on SOE's part.  Kinda like legalizing drugs.  Can't stop it.  Can't enforce it.  Might as well get a piece of the action.
<br />

<br />
