                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I voted Yes. 
<br />

<br />
So a person actually now has a choice on aquiring that level 65 spell, that peice of HP gear, without having to farm Acrylia for several hundred hours to pay for it. To force someone to spend hours and hours and hours farming something is senseless, really not enjoyable, and doesn't increase their knowledge of the game other then learning how to camp fight some other poor schmuck forced to do the same thing. 
<br />

<br />
Maybe instead of being miserable having to farm loot and prey someone buys their bazaar cr@p, people can actually experience new zones instead and keep up with their friends who maybe do have the time and talent to loot farm.
<br />

<br />
The economics in EQ is something I've always hated. I want to compete against mobs in battle for experience and advancement. I don't want to compete against my fellow players in racing to loot camps and prices wars in bazaar. People I hope now have a choice, without having to worry about their EULA.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=811112" target="_blank" class="postlink">Dyrel</a>
