                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I disagree Badmorda.
<br />

<br />
Though the game may be designed resulting in hyper inflated prices for level 65 spells it certainly wasnt the essence of the design of the game in the lower levels where the levels spells were within the range of an hour or 2 of your levels mobs. Current prices are unreasonable, and for many, unattainable.
<br />

<br />
There may be other games, but without a doubt none compare to the sheer depth and wonder EQ has magically given us. 
<br />

<br />
No one forces me or anyone else to play this "game", however it is not realistic to think with one's thousands of invested hours of online playing, offline research, deep interpersonal developed relationships, that one simply drops the game and moves on as they would Packman for Donkey Kong.
<br />

<br />
There is tons of things about EQ that I love, that I am awed about (currently experiencing Sol Ro for the 1st time and my brother and I are overwhelmed at the creativity, detail and wonder we're seeing here). There is also a ton of problems in this game, that if we bring to the open and discuss may be able to get resolved. Please don't dissmiss my concerns as petty whining. I love this game, and worked too damn hard at it just to throw it away, and I think with discussion it can be improved.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=811112" target="_blank" class="postlink">Dyrel</a>
