<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-style: italic">Meow</span></span></span>  I Find in charge of the plantiff.  SOE fork over the cash.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I'm not so sure.  The code for EQ is without a doubt SOE's property and they can do whatever they want with it.   Whether or not you have some sort of property right in the code for your account or in the code for the platinum in your account is a little bit murky, but there has been no clear statement on this issue from any court of which I am aware.  To my knowledge, there was a declaratory judgment action brought by a player auctions-like site against the makers of DAoC.  That suit was dropped, as far as I know, and there was no direct ruling on the merits of the player auctions company's claim that it had a property interest in the accounts it was powerleveling and selling to people.  
<br />

<br />
Regardess, I'm not convinved that anyone other than Sony has a legally-enforcable right to anything in Everquest, including a right to even have an account.  It is Sony's game, Sony's code, and they can pretty much do whatever they want with it.  If they have allowed some people like Yantis to make a lot of money by violating the Eula, that's been at Sony's peril and Yantis would surely argue that Sony's failure to enforce the EULA against him caused him to rely that Sony would not do so in the future.  Fine enough, that would probably work if Sony tried to sue Yantis for all the money he made off of everquest.  However, that argument  would certainly not work if Sony just shut down Yantis and didn't allow him to operate any more.  Yantis made his money by taking the risk of violating the EULA and he can probably successfully argue that he gets to keep that money.  He won't be able to to assert a "right" to continue to operate his business in a virtural world that is the property of Soney Online Entertainment.  The most important property right is the right to exclude, and I simply cannot imagine any court telling Sony that they can't control who does and doesn't have access to their game.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=646635" target="_blank" class="postlink">Saediien Iluvatri</a>
<br />
Coercer/Circle of the Golden Dragon/The Rathe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
