                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">"Worked too damned hard..."
<br />

<br />
One of the fundamental issues here is "pride of ownership."  How much pride do you have for an item that was gifted to you?  How about a hard won item that a slew of other folks just bought?  How many folks have felt dejected because they'd struggled to get to a new PoP plane with their guild, only to have flags removed from consideratoin?  How many of us worked to get to 60, feeling it was quite the accomplishment only to have zones like Paludal, Kurns and others open up that downright trivialize leveling?  How many of us worked hard through hell levels, only to have zones with high EXP rate and level "smoothing" brought up?  It goes on and on.
<br />

<br />
How many of use would feel great about seeing a 55th level character in full Ornate... or worse, Time Gear without so much as a guild tag by his/her name?  None of you would.  As much as I sneer at the "uber" guilds for making the game a "job" for players, the fact is that getting to Elemental planes, getting to Time is a hell of an accomplishment.  Part of the "pride of ownership" of being to those places is the gear that is unique to those zones... the "uber" gear that you can point at and say "I was there!"  IF Sony legitimizes selling items... it's only a half step away from Sony selling the items itself... imagine going to a GM in game, in the Bazaar and giving that GM your credit card number to fully tweak out your character in Time gear!  It's only a half step from that folks... and it's a half step we should NOT take.
<br />

<br />
Think about it guys.  How many games have you played that were too easy?  The graphics might've been good, the gear awesome but there was NO competition.  Same goes for story lines and a bunch of intangibles I won't go into here because I want to stick to pride of ownership... and you HAVE that investment, that pride when you walk that hard path and get there, first or last, it was still a difficult journey and you made it by God!  You are one of those who walked THAT path.... what if the path suddenly had moving sidewalks and escalators?
<br />

<br />
The game is being sold out... parcelled to the highest bidders... whiners in this case.  It's being watered down and trivialized bit by bit... Sure, some of the changes make things less tedious, but, it will be very easy to go too far and make the game TOO easy... I think it's already gone there.  The fact that I can get a character from 0 to 65 in as little as 48 hours says as much... there _should_ be bars to entry, as much as we whine about it, if they are NOT there, the game becomes boring... and I don't know about you, but, until this last spate of proposed changes, I was in it for the long haul.  5 years now, and I've been enjoying the game, if not enthusiasticaly, I'm at least still having fun... but, if this change comes about... I think I'll finally leave the game.  The irony is, I'm not even in a Time guild and probably will never be in one... nor will I ever see Time or the Elemental planes, odds on.  Because I don't care to make this game a job and from everything I've ever heard, the upper tier planes require THAT kind of dedication.  As much as I want to see that content, I have a life outside the game, and a life inside the game and I want to keep it that way.
<br />

<br />
It's sad because this game was so full of challenges that were interesting and worthy and they keep getting frittered away.  Cazic Thule went from being a top notch proving ground for 30s, to a grind location for upper 50s.  The Shawl went from being one of those quests no one did, to a quest that everyone does.  Tradeskills are once again being made second fiddle to dropped items when they should be equal to dropped items... the point being that tons of time spent building up tradeskills has been relegated to the "wasted time" bin.... 
<br />

<br />
I don't know about you, but, I don't want an arcade game that I can run through in record time.  I want a game I can sink my teeth into and enjoy over the long haul... I like the idea that EQ is basically open ended and that I can find a challenge, a good challenge, at most any level.  Please... get me OFF the trivialization bus... NOW!</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />GnarliAnna
<br />
E65.60/CT h+ 1.807khp 4.01km ft8 G++&lt;3 e++(+++) o++ T+++(+++++) L+ H++(+++) f++ g b@ c++ t+++ D++ X++</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
