                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It would cause legal issue for SOE but probably not the extent as to make the idea unworkable. Mostly if you're going to successfully litigate agaist them you're going to have to demonstrate that you lost income as a result of some negligence on SOE's behalf, say by losing items to a bug they refused to replace, and even then it's a small claims court action which is pretty cheap to run through. Also it would make scammers legally liable for theft and it's very possibly you could charge other players and SOE would have to release RL information about those individuals to the police although it may be difficult to successfully prosecute those cases which might cause some additional cost to SOE, but again a minor cost that would likely be recouped from the brokerage fees they'd take.
<br />

<br />
You would have VERY hard time sueing SOE for nerfing drop rates though since that would seem to fall into the catagory of "industry hazard" and unless you could demonstrate that the change was made to specifically target individuals who were making money I doubt such a motion would succeed. Moreso, they probably wouldn't have even bothered with the poll if they hadn't at least consulted their legal department first to see if it was too difficult to impliment. If the Alla poll tells us anything though, this will never happen as the majority of the playerbase seems opposed pretty strongly to the idea.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />e^(i*Pi) + 1 = 0</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
